race.comment: MAID OF MOOLAH (4) big jump in class when a month between runs for a decisive on-pace victory over 1400m at Newcastle in this company. Strips fitter and can lump the extra 3kg. Sure to be around the money. RUBI'S SERVE (3) loomed strongly last start when third over 1400m at Newcastle. Well in with the claim and the blinkers come off and the visors go on. LUNAITE (8) well supported on resumption when she covered ground in the run for a game win over 1200m here in Highway company. Goes just as well second up and shapes as a worthy contender. BLUE WILLOW (16) first-up for the new stable she chipped away late for a handy third over 1300m at Randwick. Stays in the mix despite rising in grade. BELLA MONTAGNA (1) tough mare who can surprise at this level with the two trials.
